The pipes and redirections are used to send (or retrieve) some information sent from one command or script to another command or script/files
$ grep =searches for given pattern in the output(file or output from another command)
$ grep 'case' .bashrc =searches for pattern case in a file .bashrc
$ wc -l  .bashrc = counts lines in .bashrc file
$ sort =sorts the output in alphabetical order
$ command1 | command2
$ sort | uniq

redirect to file: 
> 
If file doesn't exist, create it
Add content from redirected output
If file exists and it is not empty, clear the file and write the redirected output in empty file

>>
appends to the file

redirect from file:
<




